            <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                            <h2>Making friends</h2>
                            <div>
                                <p>While studying is very important, your social life is also a huge part of your study abroad experience. We'll make it easy for you get involved, meet new people and make friends.</p>
<p>Our staff will organise regular social activities and help you enjoy Manchester to the fullest. By taking part in our social programme you'll have the chance to meet other students and explore sights in Manchester and beyond.</p>
<p>Regular events include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Various sporting activities</li>
<li>Trips to famous sights e.g. Old Trafford football stadium</li>
<li>Trips to areas of natural beauty such as the Peak District</li>
<li>Events celebrating Chinese New Year, Eid, Christmas and Halloween</li>
</ul>

                            </div>
                </div>
            </section>
                                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Food on campus</h2>
                    <div>
                        <p>If you're feeling hungry, our café serves a range of snacks and drinks. There's also plenty of student hangouts close by including restaurants and bars.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
                    <section class="l-page-block l-text-block bottom-line">
                <div class="l-content-container">
                    <h2>Health and safety</h2>
                    <div>
                        <p>At INTO Manchester, your safety is our priority. There's a 24-hour emergency telephone helpline if you need to speak to someone outside of office hours. If you're under 18, we offer extra support including ensuring your safe transfer from the airport and checking on you every day where you live. You'll also be given a named dedicated person to contact  to ensure your wellbeing.</p>
<p>We'll also make sure you know how to register with a doctor or contact the police, as part of your induction. Of course, if you have any questions or need help with anything during your time as an INTO student we're always here to help!</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        

